{
    "rukus": [
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 1,
            "text": "He (Muhammed) frowned and turned his back"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 2,
            "text": "that the blind man came to him"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 3,
            "text": "And what will make you realize that he might have purified himself"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 4,
            "text": "or be reminded, so that (your) reminding might have profited him"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 5,
            "text": "As for him who is carefree (wealthy)"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 6,
            "text": "to him then, you pay attention"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 7,
            "text": "And if he does not purify himself, the responsibility is not on you"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 8,
            "text": "And as for him who comes to you striving hard"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 9,
            "text": "and he fears"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 10,
            "text": "from him you are distracted"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 11,
            "text": "No, it is certainly a reminder"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 12,
            "text": "so whoever wills let him remember it"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 13,
            "text": "(It is) in pages honoured"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 14,
            "text": "elevated, clean"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 15,
            "text": "in the hands of writers"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 16,
            "text": "honoured, virtuous"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 17,
            "text": "Perished be man, how ungrateful he is"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 18,
            "text": "From what thing did He create him"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 19,
            "text": "He created him from a sperm, then programmed him (to follow a certain path)"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 20,
            "text": "then, He eased that path for him"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 21,
            "text": "Then He causes him to die then buries him"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 22,
            "text": "Then, when He wills, He will raise him"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 23,
            "text": "No, he has not done that which He commanded him to do"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 24,
            "text": "So let man look at his food"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 25,
            "text": "How We pour water in the form of rain"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 26,
            "text": "then We split the earth, (with) a splitting"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 27,
            "text": "then We cause to grow therein, grain"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 28,
            "text": "and grapes and green fodder"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 29,
            "text": "and olive trees and date palms"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 30,
            "text": "and dense gardens"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 31,
            "text": "and fruits and herbage"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 32,
            "text": "A provision for you and for your cattle"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 33,
            "text": "Then when the deafening sound comes"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 34,
            "text": "(it will be) a day when man will run away from his brother"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 35,
            "text": "and his mother and his father"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 36,
            "text": "and his wife and his sons"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 37,
            "text": "on that day, for everyone of them there will be enough concern to keep him unconcerned with others"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 38,
            "text": "(Some) faces on that day will be bright"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 39,
            "text": "laughing, rejoicing at the good news"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 40,
            "text": "(while other) faces on that day will have dust over them"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 41,
            "text": "being covered with darkness"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 80,
            "verse": 42,
            "text": "Those are the infidels, the transgressors"
        }
    ]
}